The paper discusses the topic of explainability in artificial intelligence, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on the interpretability of machine learning models and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of explanations for algorithmic fairness and identifying potential bias/problems in the training data, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.CY (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper also discusses the challenges of current approaches to explanatory methods, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
